{"_id":"Brandiedchickenliverpate","preptime":"10","servings":"6","keywords":["cook method.hob, oven, grill@hob","special collections@classic recipe","meal type@starters","diet@corn-free","occasion@entertaining","scalability@fun for one","occasion@christmas","diet@egg-free","meal type@lunch / snacks","occasion@prepare-ahead entertaining","diet@wheat-free","diet@peanut-free","diet@citrus-free","diet@shellfish-free","scalability@good for numbers","diet@gluten-free"],"subtitle":"","totaltime":"17","cooktime":"7","ingredients":[{"ingredient":"chicken livers","measure":"450 g"},{"ingredient":"butter","measure":"40 g"},{"ingredient":"vegetable oil","measure":"6 tsp"},{"ingredient":"onion","measure":"1"},{"ingredient":"garlic","measure":"1 clove"},{"ingredient":"double cream","measure":"60 ml"},{"ingredient":"tomato puree","measure":"3 tsp"},{"ingredient":"brandy","measure":"6 tsp"},{"ingredient":"seasoning","measure":""},{"ingredient":"fresh parsley","measure":"3 tsp"}],"method":[{"step":"1","text":"Dry the chicken livers on kitchen paper. "},{"step":"2","text":"In a frying pan, heat the butter and oil together. Gently fry the onion and garlic for 2-3 min or until just soft."},{"step":"3","text":"Stir in the chicken livers and cook for 5-6 min. Leave to cool. "},{"step":"4","text":"Add the cream, tomato puree, brandy and seasoning. Place in a food processor. Blend until smooth. Fold in the parsley."},{"step":"5","text":"Spoon into a serving dish."}],"title":"Brandied chicken liver pate"}